  id: Forepaw_Digit3_Distal_R
  partName: Forepaw Digit3 Distal Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right forepaw digit three distal phalanx is the terminal bone of the third
    digit located at the end of the canine toe. This structure supports the claw
    and serves as an attachment point for tendons controlling digital movement.
  - It contributes to traction, digging, gripping, and stability during locomotion
    and weight-bearing activities. The distal phalanx also protects sensitive tissues
    within the claw region while supporting proper paw mechanics during walking and
    running.
